<thead>

<tr>

<td></td>

<td>Cultural sensitivity</td>

<td> Cultural competence</td>

<td>Cultural humility</td>

</tr>

</thead>

<tbody>

<tr>

<td>Main focus</td>

<td>Avoiding obvious offence; basic awareness (e.g. festivals, food).</td>

<td>Skills, protocols and knowledge about difference (e.g. working with interpreters).</td>

<td>Ethical relationship, shared power and ongoing learning with people and communities.</td>

</tr>





<tr>

<td>Risks if used alone</td>

<td>Stereotypes and token gestures (e.g. “cultural days” with no deeper change).</td>

<td>Checklist mindset and “expert on others”; limited attention to power or history.</td>

<td>Can feel uncomfortable and time-consuming without organisational support.</td>

</tr>





<tr>

<td>Best use</td>

<td>Courtesy and respectful starting points in day-to-day interactions.</td>

<td>Reliable procedures (e.g. referral pathways, interpreter use, information standards).</td>

<td>Guiding values for decisions, system design and accountability.</td>

</tr>

</tbody>

</table>















